<i>to play the game?</i>

03:24.204 --> 03:25.621
<i>[ Audience continues cheering ]</i>

03:25.788 --> 03:27.748
<i>STEVE: Everyone at home,</i>
<i>are you ready?</i>

03:27.749 --> 03:29.875
<i>[ Audience continues cheering ]</i>

03:30.376 --> 03:33.587
<i>STEVE: As you can see, our first</i>
<i>puzzle of the day is a sentence.</i>

03:34.589 --> 03:36.882
Can we have this television
turned off, please?

03:36.883 --> 03:37.799
No.

03:37.800 --> 03:39.885
<i>STEVE: The movie ''White Heat''</i>
<i>starred James Cagney...</i>

03:39.886 --> 03:40.761
Leave it on.

03:40.762 --> 03:42.846
<i>STEVE: ...Kirk Douglas,</i>
<i>or Humphrey Bogart?</i>

03:43.056 --> 03:44.097
<i>All right, Ron.</i>

03:44.098 --> 03:45.474
<i>-RON: Cagney.</i>
<i>-STEVE: Right answer, Ron.</i>

03:45.475 --> 03:46.308
<i>STEVE: Pick a letter.</i>

03:46.559 --> 03:47.517
<i>RON: How about an ''S''?</i>

03:47.769 --> 03:48.936
<i>STEVE: Yes, there is.</i>

03:49.103 --> 03:50.729
<i>[ Audience cheering ]</i>

03:53.942 --> 03:57.527
<i>-A ''B''. Just get a ''B''.</i>
<i>- [ Audience cheering ]</i>

03:58.571 --> 03:59.988
<i>-RON: How about an ''R''?</i>
<i>-PRISONER: An ''R''.</i>

